<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="utf-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
<title>UK Day Trips &mdash; July 2026 &middot; Cannock base</title>
<style>
:root{--bg:#0f1216;--card:#1a1f27;--card2:#222834;--ink:#eef2f7;--mut:#9aa7b6;--acc:#5cc8ff;--warm:#ffb454;--line:#2b333f;--good:#8be28b}
*{box-sizing:border-box}
body{margin:0;background:var(--bg);color:var(--ink);font:16px/1.5 -apple-system,BlinkMacSystemFont,"Segoe UI",Roboto,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif}
header{padding:26px 18px 14px;background:linear-gradient(160deg,#1c2530,#0f1216)}
h1{margin:0 0 4px;font-size:22px}
.sub{color:var(--mut);font-size:14px}
.wrap{max-width:720px;margin:0 auto;padding:0 14px 60px}
.note{background:var(--card2);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:14px;padding:14px 16px;margin:16px 0;font-size:14.5px}
.note b{color:var(--warm)}
.bar{display:flex;justify-content:flex-end;margin:6px 0 0}
#showall{background:var(--card2);color:var(--acc);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:20px;padding:6px 14px;font-size:13px;font-weight:600;cursor:pointer}
.day{background:var(--card);border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:18px;overflow:hidden;margin:16px 0;box-shadow:0 6px 20px rgba(0,0,0,.25);transition:opacity .2s}
.day img{width:100%;height:210px;object-fit:cover;display:block;background:#222}
.body{padding:14px 16px 18px}
.tag{display:inline-block;font-size:12px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.3px;color:#0f1216;background:var(--acc);border-radius:20px;padding:3px 10px;margin-bottom:8px}
.tag.rest{background:var(--warm)}
.tag.flex{background:var(--good)}
.dt{font-size:19px;font-weight:700;margin:2px 0 2px}
.drive{color:var(--mut);font-size:13.5px;margin-bottom:10px}
p.desc{margin:8px 0 12px;font-size:15px;color:#dfe6ee}
.links a{display:inline-block;margin:4px 8px 4px 0;font-size:13.5px;color:var(--acc);text-decoration:none;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:20px;padding:5px 12px}
.links a:active{background:var(--card2)}
a.map{background:#243244;border-color:#2f4256;color:#bfe0ff}
a.ask{background:#2a1f33;border-color:#4b3a5c;color:#e6b8ff}
.cap{font-size:11px;color:#6b7686;padding:0 16px 12px}
details{margin:6px 0 4px;border-top:1px solid var(--line);padding-top:8px}
summary{cursor:pointer;color:var(--acc);font-size:13.5px;font-weight:600;list-style:none;outline:none}
summary::-webkit-details-marker{display:none}
summary::after{content:" \25BE"}
details[open] summary::after{content:" \25B4"}
details.alt summary{color:var(--warm)}
.route{background:#141b24;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:10px 14px 8px;margin:12px 0 4px}
.route .rt{font-size:13.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--acc);margin-bottom:6px}
.route ol{margin:0;padding-left:20px}
.route li{font-size:14px;color:#eef2f7;margin:6px 0}
.route li b{color:#fff}
.route .leg{display:block;color:var(--mut);font-size:12.5px;margin-top:1px}
.rmaplink{position:relative;display:block;margin:4px 0 10px}
.rmap{width:100%;height:auto;border-radius:10px;border:1px solid var(--line);display:block}
.rmap-hint{position:absolute;right:8px;bottom:8px;background:rgba(15,18,22,.86);color:#eef2f7;font-size:11.5px;font-weight:600;padding:4px 9px;border-radius:20px;border:1px solid var(--line);pointer-events:none}
.rmaplink:active .rmap{filter:brightness(.9)}
.cmp{background:#141b24;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:12px;padding:12px 14px;margin:12px 0 4px}
.cmp-h{font-size:14px;font-weight:700;color:var(--acc);margin-bottom:4px}
.cmp-row{border-top:1px solid var(--line);padding:8px 0}
.cmp-k{font-size:12.5px;font-weight:700;color:var(--warm);margin-bottom:3px}
.cmp-a,.cmp-b{font-size:13.5px;color:#dfe6ee;margin:2px 0}
.cmp-a b,.cmp-b b{color:#fff}
.opt-h{font-size:15px;font-weight:700;color:#eef2f7;margin:16px 0 0}
.cmp a{color:var(--acc);font-weight:600;text-decoration:none}
.cmp a:active{opacity:.7}
.cmp a.map{background:#243244;border:1px solid #2f4256;color:#bfe0ff;border-radius:20px;padding:3px 10px;font-size:12.5px;display:inline-block;margin-top:4px}
.ql{font-size:13.5px;color:#dfe6ee;margin:6px 0;padding-left:2px}
.det{font-size:14px;color:#dfe6ee}
.det ul{margin:8px 0 4px 18px;padding:0}
.det li{margin:6px 0}
.det b{color:#fff}
footer{color:var(--mut);font-size:12.5px;text-align:center;padding:20px}
.badge{display:inline-block;font-size:10.5px;font-weight:700;color:#0f1216;background:var(--acc);border-radius:6px;padding:1px 6px;margin-left:8px;vertical-align:middle}
.day.today{border-color:var(--acc);box-shadow:0 0 0 2px rgba(92,200,255,.35)}
.day.past{opacity:.5}
.day.past img,.day.past .desc,.day.past .drive,.day.past .links,.day.past details{display:none}
.day.past .body{padding:11px 16px}
.day.past .tag{display:none}
.day.past .dt{font-size:15px;font-weight:600;color:var(--mut)}
.day.past .dt::before{content:"\2713  ";color:var(--good);font-weight:700}
body.show-past .day.past{opacity:.85}
body.show-past .day.past img,body.show-past .day.past .desc,body.show-past .day.past .drive,body.show-past .day.past .links,body.show-past .day.past details{display:block}
body.show-past .day.past .tag{display:inline-block}
body.show-past .day.past .dt{font-size:19px;font-weight:700;color:var(--ink)}
body.show-past .day.past .dt::before{content:""}
</style>
</head>
<body>
<header>
  <div class="wrap" style="padding-bottom:0">
    <h1>&#128663; UK Day Trips &mdash; July 2026</h1>
    <div class="sub">Based at Cannock, Staffordshire &middot; baby-friendly + historic + scenery &middot; home each night</div>
  </div>
</header>
<div class="wrap">

  <div class="note">
    &#9728;&#65039; <b>Weather &mdash; re-checked 11 Jul (Met Office):</b> high pressure is firmly settled &rarr; <b>dry, sunny &amp; warm every day</b>, a comfortable <b>25&ndash;29&deg;C</b> with rain under 20% right through to Thu 16. No wet days to work around this week &mdash; the plan is slotted by <b>drive distance and Alfie&rsquo;s stamina</b> instead (long hauls on the quieter weekdays, shady/air-con options for the hottest afternoons). Re-check North Wales (Sun 12) ~48h out for the breeze. Every day has an <b>Alternatives</b> tab if you fancy a swap.<br>
    &#128204; <b>Fri 10 was pool + BBQ + the Gruffalo trail</b> (too hot/exposed) &mdash; day trips run <b>Sat 11&ndash;Wed 15</b>. <b>Thu 16 the car goes back:</b> drive to Birmingham, shop, train home. Fri 17 = London.<br>
    <b>Tip:</b> tap <b>&quot;Where to go &amp; options&quot;</b> on any day for exact spots &amp; baby-friendly ideas, or <b>&quot;Ask for more&quot;</b> to have detail added.
  </div>
  <div class="bar"><button id="showall">Show past days</button></div>
  <div class="day" data-date="2026-07-10">
    
    <div class="body">
      <span class="tag rest">Fri 10 Jul &middot; family day</span>
      <div class="dt">Pool day + BBQ at your sister&rsquo;s</div>
      <div class="drive">&#9201; no driving &middot; hottest day of the week (~33&deg;C)</div>
      <p class="desc">Pool + BBQ at your sister&rsquo;s, with the Gruffalo trail at Cannock Chase in the morning &mdash; but it was too hot with not enough shade, so the rest of the week leans into air-con, water and tree cover. The day trips proper kick off Sat 11.</p>
      
      
      <details><summary>About this plan</summary><div class="det">A mix for everyone this week &mdash; a <b>relaxed indoor-shopping day for Phoebe</b> (Sat), a <b>seaside day in North Wales on Sunday with your sister</b>, <b>Drayton Manor&rsquo;s Thomas Land</b> for Alfie (Mon, with your sister &amp; Jess), a <b>Peak District scenic loop</b> (with the Chatsworth Farm Shop, Tue), and a <b>designer-outlet day</b> (your pick of Cheshire Oaks, or Bicester Village + Oxford, Wed). Hot afternoons favour shade, water and the air-conditioned car. <b>The rental car goes back on Thu 16</b>, so all the driving is Sat&ndash;Wed and Thursday is a car-free Birmingham town day.</div></details>
      
      <div class="links"><a class="ask" href="https://zlviiufrnx354pyk6bc9vy9dauofbwvq.ui.nabu.casa/trip-ask?a=the%20UK%20week">Ask for more &#8599;</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="day" data-date="2026-07-11">
    
    <div class="body">
      <span class="tag">Sat 11 Jul &middot; sunny, 29&deg;</span>
      <div class="dt">Relaxed day &mdash; Phoebe&rsquo;s shopping pick</div>
      <div class="drive">&#9201; a relaxed one &middot; indoor shopping + the footy tonight</div>
      <p class="desc">An easy day &mdash; you&rsquo;ve already done the Cannock outlet, so today is an indoor-shopping day of Phoebe&rsquo;s choosing (options below), staying cool on a hot one. Then the <b>England v Norway World Cup quarter-final tonight</b>.</p>
      
      <div class="cmp"><div class="cmp-h">&#128717; Indoor shopping for today &mdash; two bigger options (for Phoebe)</div><div class="cmp-a" style="margin:2px 0 2px">Both ~30&ndash;40 min, air-conditioned, and fresh (not Thursday&rsquo;s Birmingham):</div><div class="cmp-row"><div class="cmp-k">Touchwood, Solihull &middot; ~40 min &mdash; the classier pick</div><div class="cmp-a">John Lewis flagship + Apple + Zara / Mango / Next, and designer near House of Fraser; 20+ restaurants, a cinema and easy parking &mdash; calmer with a toddler. <a href="https://www.touchwoodsolihull.co.uk/">Site &#8599;</a> &nbsp;<a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Touchwood+Solihull">Map &#8599;</a></div></div><div class="cmp-row"><div class="cmp-k">Merry Hill, Dudley &middot; ~30 min &mdash; the most choice</div><div class="cmp-a">180&ndash;250 shops, fashion-heavy (M&amp;S, Next, Primark + womenswear &amp; beauty), mostly under cover with big free parking. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Merry+Hill+Shopping+Centre+Dudley">Map &#8599;</a></div></div></div><div class="cmp"><div class="cmp-h">&#128279; Quick-check other options for today</div><div class="ql">&bull; <a href="https://bullring.co.uk/">Bullring &amp; Grand Central, Birmingham &#8599;</a> &mdash; the most shops + Selfridges (note: also your Thursday stop)</div><div class="ql">&bull; <a href="https://www.harveynichols.com/store/birmingham/guide/">Harvey Nichols, The Mailbox &#8599;</a> &mdash; proper luxury + beauty rooms / treatments</div><div class="ql">&bull; <a href="https://www.resortsworldbirmingham.co.uk/shop">Resorts World Birmingham &#8599;</a> &mdash; fully-indoor outlet + spa + cinema under one roof</div><div class="ql">&bull; <a href="https://trentham.co.uk/">Trentham Shopping Village + Gardens, Stoke &#8599;</a> &mdash; indie boutiques &amp; homeware by the Italian gardens</div><div class="ql">&bull; <a href="https://www.experiencesolihull.co.uk/">Solihull town + Touchwood &#8599;</a> &nbsp;&middot;&nbsp; <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=West+Midlands+shopping+centres">more nearby on the map &#8599;</a></div></div>
      <details><summary>Handy for today</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>&#9917; Tonight:</b> England v Norway, World Cup quarter-final, <b>10pm kick-off</b>. With Alfie that&rsquo;s a late one &mdash; easiest to watch at your dad&rsquo;s or sister&rsquo;s once he&rsquo;s down; or, with a sitter, <b>Bar Sport Cannock</b> (book ahead, it&rsquo;ll be packed) or the Royal Oak.</li><li><b>Staying cool:</b> ~29&deg;C today &mdash; the shopping centres below are all air-conditioned; carry water for Alfie.</li><li><b>Fancy an outing instead?</b> West Midland Safari Park or Waterworld (Stoke) are still there if you&rsquo;d rather a day out than shops &mdash; just ask and I&rsquo;ll plan it.</li></ul></div></details>
      
      <div class="links"><a class="ask" href="https://zlviiufrnx354pyk6bc9vy9dauofbwvq.ui.nabu.casa/trip-ask?a=today%20(relaxed%20%2F%20shopping)">Ask for more &#8599;</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="day" data-date="2026-07-12">
    <img loading="lazy" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="North Wales &mdash; Conwy + Llandudno"><div class="cap">Conwy Castle &middot; Wikimedia Commons</div>
    <div class="body">
      <span class="tag">Sun 12 Jul &middot; seaside, breezy</span>
      <div class="dt">North Wales &mdash; Conwy + Llandudno</div>
      <div class="drive">&#9201; scenic loop ~237 mi (or ~210 mi out-and-back) &middot; with your sister</div>
      <p class="desc">The seaside day, out with your sister. Conwy is a spectacular walled town with one of Europe&rsquo;s best-preserved castles on the estuary; then 10 min to Llandudno&rsquo;s grand Victorian seaside prom (flat, pram-perfect), a sandy beach for a paddle and the Great Orme tram. Drive out along the fast A55 coast road, and &mdash; if everyone&rsquo;s up for it &mdash; come home the scenic way south past the <b>Pontcysyllte Aqueduct</b> and <b>Llangollen</b> (see the map). Too tired? Just retrace the A55, which knocks ~1h15 off. It&rsquo;s the biggest driving day of the week, so set off early.</p>
      <div class="route"><div class="rt">&#128506;&#65039; The planned loop &mdash; ~237 mi, ~5h driving (or ~210 mi out-and-back)</div><a class="rmaplink" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Cannock/Conwy+Castle/Llandudno/Pontcysyllte+Aqueduct/Llangollen/Cannock" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="rmap" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Route map"><span class="rmap-hint">&#128205; Tap for live directions &#8599;</span></a><ol><li><b>&#9312;&rarr;&#9313; &nbsp;Home (Cannock) &rarr; Conwy</b><span class="leg">~108 mi &middot; ~2h15 &mdash; <b>out</b> along the fast A55 North Wales coast road</span></li><li><b>&#9313; &nbsp;Conwy &rarr; Llandudno</b><span class="leg">~4 mi &middot; ~12 min &mdash; round the estuary to the seaside prom</span></li><li><b>&#9313;&rarr;&#9314; &nbsp;Llandudno &rarr; Llangollen / Pontcysyllte</b><span class="leg">~63 mi &middot; ~1h20 &mdash; <b>scenic return:</b> south down the A470 Conwy valley, then the A5 to the aqueduct</span></li><li><b>&#9314;&rarr;&#9312; &nbsp;Llangollen &rarr; home (Cannock)</b><span class="leg">~62 mi &middot; ~1h20 &mdash; A5 / A483 south-east back to base</span></li><li><b>&#128299; Tired? Shorter return</b><span class="leg">skip Llangollen and retrace the <b>A55 coast</b> from Llandudno &mdash; ~105 mi / ~1h45 straight home (saves ~1h15)</span></li></ol></div>
      
      <details><summary>Where to go &amp; options</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>Conwy:</b> the castle has steep spiral steps (carrier, not pram, inside); the walkable town walls, the quay, and the <b>Smallest House in Britain</b> are all easy. Good chippy/cafes on the quay.</li><li><b>Llandudno:</b> the flat Victorian promenade and pier are pram-perfect; ride the <b>Great Orme Tramway</b> or cable car for big views; sandy beach for a paddle.</li><li><b>If you want gardens:</b> <b>Bodnant Garden</b> (NT) is ~20 min inland &mdash; buggy-friendly terraces.</li><li><b>Logistics:</b> the biggest driving day of the week &mdash; ~210 mi out-and-back, or ~237 mi with the scenic Llangollen return (see the route map). Leave ~9am; pack sun cream and a wind layer for the prom, plus snacks.</li></ul></div></details>
      <details class="alt"><summary>&#128260; Alternatives for this day</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>&#128299; Skip the scenic loop</b> &mdash; if it&rsquo;s a long day, just come straight back on the <b>A55</b> from Llandudno (~1h45) instead of the A5/Llangollen return. Saves ~1h15. <a class="map" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Llandudno/Cannock">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Rhyl &amp; Prestatyn</b> (~1h20, closer coast) &mdash; long sandy beaches plus the indoor <b>SC2</b> waterpark at Rhyl if it&rsquo;s hot. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Rhyl+beach">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Great Orme, Llandudno</b> &mdash; ride the tram or cable car to the summit; the Bronze-Age copper mine is a cool, shaded add-on. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Great+Orme+Llandudno">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Bodnant Garden (NT)</b> (~20 min inland from Conwy) &mdash; buggy-friendly terraced gardens if you fancy less beach. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Bodnant+Garden">Map &#8599;</a></li></ul></div></details>
      <div class="links"><a href="https://cadw.gov.wales/visit/places-to-visit/conwy-castle">Conwy Castle &#8599;</a><a href="https://www.visitllandudno.org.uk/">Visit Llandudno &#8599;</a><a class="map" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Cannock/Conwy+Castle">Directions &#8599;</a><a class="ask" href="https://zlviiufrnx354pyk6bc9vy9dauofbwvq.ui.nabu.casa/trip-ask?a=Conwy%20%2B%20Llandudno%20(North%20Wales)">Ask for more &#8599;</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="day" data-date="2026-07-13">
    <img loading="lazy" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Drayton Manor + Thomas Land"><div class="cap">Thomas Land, Drayton Manor &middot; Wikimedia Commons</div>
    <div class="body">
      <span class="tag">Mon 13 Jul &middot; sunny, 27&deg;</span>
      <div class="dt">Drayton Manor + Thomas Land</div>
      <div class="drive">&#9201; ~30 min each way (Tamworth) &middot; with your sister &amp; Jess</div>
      <p class="desc">The big one for Alfie &mdash; and <b>your sister and Jess are coming along too</b>. A nice easy day right after Sunday&rsquo;s Wales run: Europe&rsquo;s only <b>Thomas Land</b> &mdash; a whole area of rides scaled for little ones &mdash; plus a 15-acre zoo. The single best all-round toddler day, and a great one to share. Book online in advance: much cheaper than the gate (roughly &pound;28&ndash;34 online vs ~&pound;40 on the day).</p>
      
      
      <details><summary>Where to go &amp; options</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>Thomas Land:</b> ~25 rides themed around Thomas &amp; Friends, most gentle enough for toddlers (some have a minimum height, so pack the buggy for the in-betweens). Open ~10:30&ndash;16:00.</li><li><b>Drayton Manor Zoo:</b> 15 acres included with entry &mdash; meerkats, monkeys, reptiles and a walk-through aviary; a good cool-down from the rides.</li><li><b>With your sister &amp; Jess:</b> a group day &mdash; book everyone&rsquo;s tickets online together (same entry) and meet at the gate for opening. Do Thomas Land first while Alfie&rsquo;s fresh, then the zoo / lunch after his nap.</li><li><b>Easy day:</b> just a ~30-min hop the day after Sunday&rsquo;s Wales run &mdash; home for an afternoon nap with plenty of the day left, before Tuesday&rsquo;s Peak loop.</li></ul></div></details>
      <details class="alt"><summary>&#128260; Alternatives for this day</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>Alton Towers &mdash; CBeebies Land</b> (~40 min) &mdash; a whole area aimed at toddlers (the rest of the park is thrill rides). Pre-book online. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Alton+Towers">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Trentham Monkey Forest + Gardens</b> (~35 min) &mdash; free-roaming macaques on a woodland walk, plus gardens and a big playground. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Trentham+Monkey+Forest">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Twycross Zoo</b> (~35 min) &mdash; big zoo with indoor soft-play for a hot afternoon. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Twycross+Zoo">Map &#8599;</a></li></ul></div></details>
      <div class="links"><a href="https://www.draytonmanor.co.uk/">Drayton Manor &#8599;</a><a href="https://www.draytonmanor.co.uk/thomas-land">Thomas Land &#8599;</a><a class="map" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Cannock/Drayton+Manor+Resort">Directions &#8599;</a><a class="ask" href="https://zlviiufrnx354pyk6bc9vy9dauofbwvq.ui.nabu.casa/trip-ask?a=Drayton%20Manor%20%2B%20Thomas%20Land">Ask for more &#8599;</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="day" data-date="2026-07-14">
    <img loading="lazy" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Peak District loop &mdash; Castleton, Bakewell &amp; Chatsworth"><div class="cap">Winnats Pass, Peak District &middot; Wikimedia Commons</div>
    <div class="body">
      <span class="tag">Tue 14 Jul &middot; scenic loop, sunny 27&deg;</span>
      <div class="dt">Peak District loop &mdash; Castleton, Bakewell &amp; Chatsworth</div>
      <div class="drive">&#9201; a full scenic loop (~146 mi round) &middot; out one way, back another</div>
      <p class="desc">The dramatic drive AND the shopping, as a proper loop that hits the good spots both ways. Head up the A515 to the High Peak first &mdash; the plunge down <b>Winnats Pass</b>, the ridge of <b>Mam Tor</b> and the stone village of <b>Castleton</b> &mdash; then across to <b>Bakewell</b> and <b>Chatsworth</b> for its famous Farm Shop and the farmyard/playground for Alfie. Come home a different, scenic way: south down the A6 through the <b>Derwent gorge past Matlock Bath</b>. A big, driving-heavy day, but scenery and shopping both sorted &mdash; see the map below.</p>
      <div class="route"><div class="rt">&#128506;&#65039; The planned loop &mdash; ~146 mi, ~4h driving (plus stops)</div><a class="rmaplink" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Cannock/Winnats+Pass/Castleton/Bakewell/Chatsworth+House/Matlock+Bath/Cannock" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="rmap" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Route map"><span class="rmap-hint">&#128205; Tap for live directions &#8599;</span></a><ol><li><b>&#9312;&rarr;&#9313; &nbsp;Home (Cannock) &rarr; Winnats Pass &amp; Castleton</b><span class="leg">~58 mi &middot; ~1h35 &mdash; <b>out</b> north up the A515 through Ashbourne and the White Peak dales; drive Winnats Pass down into Castleton</span></li><li><b>&#9313;&rarr;&#9314; &nbsp;Castleton &rarr; Bakewell</b><span class="leg">~14 mi &middot; ~25 min &mdash; A6187 down the Hope Valley, then the A6 south</span></li><li><b>&#9314;&rarr;&#9315; &nbsp;Bakewell &rarr; Chatsworth</b><span class="leg">~5 mi &middot; ~15 min &mdash; A619 to Baslow, then the B6012 along the Derwent (Farm Shop &amp; house)</span></li><li><b>&#9315;&rarr;&#9316; &nbsp;Chatsworth &rarr; Matlock Bath</b><span class="leg">~13 mi &middot; ~30 min &mdash; <b>back a different way:</b> south down the scenic A6 through the Derwent gorge</span></li><li><b>&#9316;&rarr;&#9312; &nbsp;Matlock Bath &rarr; home (Cannock)</b><span class="leg">~55 mi &middot; ~1h20 &mdash; A6 / A38 south</span></li></ol></div>
      
      <details><summary>The loop &amp; stops</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>Winnats Pass &amp; Mam Tor:</b> drive the steep limestone gorge slowly (it&rsquo;s spectacular), then pull in on the Mam Tor ridge for the Hope Valley panorama (paragliders often launch here). Carrier, not pram, for the short steep bits.</li><li><b>Castleton:</b> a pretty village for a coffee and ice cream, with the ruined Peveril Castle above; the <b>Blue John / Treak Cliff caverns</b> are a cool option on a hot day (check suitability with a toddler).</li><li><b>Bakewell:</b> the classic Peak market town &mdash; independent shops, riverside walks and the original Bakewell pudding shops. (The big stall market is Mondays only, so it won&rsquo;t be on today, but the town&rsquo;s lovely regardless.)</li><li><b>Chatsworth:</b> the estate &mdash; the renowned <b>Farm Shop</b> at Pilsley (craft butcher, on-site bakery, a deli with 104 cheeses, local treats + Peak Ales) and, if there&rsquo;s time, the farmyard, adventure playground and parkland for Alfie.</li><li><b>Matlock Bath (on the way home):</b> come back the scenic way down the A6 through the Derwent gorge &mdash; this riverside resort (&ldquo;Little Switzerland&rdquo;) is a fun stop for an ice cream, the cable car up to the <b>Heights of Abraham</b>, or just a stroll by the water.</li><li><b>With Alfie:</b> it&rsquo;s a long, driving-heavy day (~146 mi, ~4h at the wheel) &mdash; pick the highlights rather than everything, plan stops around naps, and be ready to trim the caverns, the house or Matlock if he&rsquo;s had enough (the <b>Alternatives</b> tab has a much shorter version).</li></ul></div></details>
      <details class="alt"><summary>&#128260; Alternatives for this day</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>Shorten it:</b> skip the High Peak and just do <b>Bakewell + Chatsworth</b> via Ashbourne and the dales (~1h each way) &mdash; all the shopping, far less driving. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Bakewell">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Shropshire Hills / Long Mynd</b> (~1h) &mdash; a scenic drive over the tops to <b>Carding Mill Valley</b> (NT), a gentle stream walk for Alfie. Closer, softer scenery. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Carding+Mill+Valley">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Buxton</b> (~1h) &mdash; elegant spa town: the Victorian <b>Cavendish Arcade</b> shops, Pavilion Gardens (pram-friendly) and the Crescent. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Buxton+Derbyshire">Map &#8599;</a></li></ul></div></details>
      <div class="links"><a href="https://www.visitpeakdistrict.com/explore/castleton">Castleton &#8599;</a><a href="https://www.chatsworth.org/visit-chatsworth/shop-dine-stay/farm-shop/">Chatsworth Farm Shop &#8599;</a><a href="https://www.visitpeakdistrict.com/explore/matlock-bath">Matlock Bath &#8599;</a><a class="map" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Cannock/Winnats+Pass/Castleton/Bakewell/Chatsworth+House/Matlock+Bath/Cannock">Open the loop in Maps &#8599;</a><a class="ask" href="https://zlviiufrnx354pyk6bc9vy9dauofbwvq.ui.nabu.casa/trip-ask?a=Peak%20District%20loop%20(Castleton%20%2F%20Bakewell%20%2F%20Chatsworth)">Ask for more &#8599;</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="day" data-date="2026-07-15">
    <img loading="lazy" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Shopping day &mdash; two options"><div class="cap">Oxford skyline from St Mary&rsquo;s &middot; Wikimedia Commons</div>
    <div class="body">
      <span class="tag">Wed 15 Jul &middot; sunny, 28&deg;</span>
      <div class="dt">Shopping day &mdash; two options</div>
      <div class="drive">&#9201; pick one &middot; ~152 mi (Cheshire Oaks) or ~190 mi (Bicester + Oxford) &middot; last car day</div>
      <p class="desc">A designer-outlet day &mdash; and your last full day with the car. Two very different ways to do it: either a quicker, relaxed run up to <b>Cheshire Oaks</b> near Chester, or a bigger day south pairing luxury shopping at <b>Bicester Village</b> with an afternoon in <b>Oxford</b>. Here&rsquo;s how they stack up &mdash; each with its own route map &mdash; then take your pick.</p>
      
      <div class="cmp"><div class="cmp-h">&#128717; Two ways to do the outlet day &mdash; how they compare</div><div class="cmp-row"><div class="cmp-k">&#128663; Drive</div><div class="cmp-a"><b>Cheshire Oaks:</b> ~152 mi round &middot; ~2h55 driving (NW, near Chester)</div><div class="cmp-b"><b>Bicester + Oxford:</b> ~190 mi round &middot; ~4h driving (south, down the M40)</div></div><div class="cmp-row"><div class="cmp-k">&#128337; Shape of the day</div><div class="cmp-a"><b>Cheshire Oaks:</b> a relaxed half-day of pure outlet shopping &mdash; home in good time; easy to bolt on Chester Zoo / Blue Planet Aquarium.</div><div class="cmp-b"><b>Bicester + Oxford:</b> a full day out &mdash; premium shopping in the morning, then a world-famous city all afternoon.</div></div><div class="cmp-row"><div class="cmp-k">&#127991;&#65039; Brands &amp; prices</div><div class="cmp-a"><b>Cheshire Oaks:</b> ~145 stores, high-street + mid-premium (Nike, Boss, M&amp;S, Le Creuset), 30&ndash;60% off.</div><div class="cmp-b"><b>Bicester Village:</b> ~160 stores, skews luxury/designer (Burberry, Gucci, Prada, Boss) &mdash; higher-end labels, 30&ndash;60% off.</div></div><div class="cmp-row"><div class="cmp-k">&#128118; With Alfie</div><div class="cmp-a"><b>Cheshire Oaks:</b> flat, pram-easy, baby-change; Blue Planet Aquarium next door (indoor).</div><div class="cmp-b"><b>Bicester + Oxford:</b> flat outlet, then more walking/history in Oxford; University Parks + the free Ashmolean; use a Park &amp; Ride.</div></div><div class="cmp-row"><div class="cmp-k">&#9989; Pick this if&hellip;</div><div class="cmp-a"><b>Cheshire Oaks</b> &mdash; you want easy + shorter + maybe animals, and home earlier for the evening.</div><div class="cmp-b"><b>Bicester + Oxford</b> &mdash; you want the luxury shopping AND a proper city day, and don&rsquo;t mind the drive.</div></div></div><div class="opt-h">Option A &mdash; Cheshire Oaks Designer Outlet</div><div class="route"><div class="rt">&#128506;&#65039; ~152 mi round &middot; ~2h55 driving</div><a class="rmaplink" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Cannock/Cheshire+Oaks+Designer+Outlet/Chester+Zoo/Cannock" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="rmap" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Route map"><span class="rmap-hint">&#128205; Tap for live directions &#8599;</span></a><ol><li><b>&#9312;&rarr;&#9313; &nbsp;Home (Cannock) &rarr; Cheshire Oaks</b><span class="leg">~76 mi &middot; ~1h25 &mdash; up the M6/M56 to Ellesmere Port</span></li><li><b>&#9313;&rarr;&#9314; &nbsp;Optional add-on: Chester Zoo</b><span class="leg">~5 mi &middot; ~12 min &mdash; world-class zoo right next door if you fancy more</span></li><li><b>&#9314;&rarr;&#9312; &nbsp;back home (Cannock)</b><span class="leg">~70 mi &middot; ~1h20</span></li></ol></div><div class="opt-h">Option B &mdash; Bicester Village + Oxford</div><div class="route"><div class="rt">&#128506;&#65039; ~190 mi round &middot; ~4h driving</div><a class="rmaplink" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Cannock/Bicester+Village/Oxford/Cannock" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><img class="rmap" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Route map"><span class="rmap-hint">&#128205; Tap for live directions &#8599;</span></a><ol><li><b>&#9312;&rarr;&#9313; &nbsp;Home (Cannock) &rarr; Bicester Village</b><span class="leg">~84 mi &middot; ~1h35 &mdash; south down the M42/M40; arrive near opening (~9&ndash;10am)</span></li><li><b>&#9313;&rarr;&#9314; &nbsp;Bicester Village &rarr; Oxford</b><span class="leg">~15 mi &middot; ~30 min &mdash; a short hop; Park &amp; Ride into the centre</span></li><li><b>&#9314;&rarr;&#9312; &nbsp;Oxford &rarr; home (Cannock)</b><span class="leg">~91 mi &middot; ~1h50 &mdash; back up the M40</span></li></ol></div>
      <details><summary>Tips for each</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>Cheshire Oaks:</b> the UK&rsquo;s biggest outlet by store count &mdash; open-air, flat, baby-change, big free-ish car park. Bolt on the <b>Blue Planet Aquarium</b> (right there) or <b>Chester Zoo</b> (12 min) to fill the day.</li><li><b>Bicester Village:</b> ~160 luxury/designer boutiques (Burberry, Gucci, Prada, Boss&hellip;), open-air &quot;village&quot; streets, very busy midday &mdash; go early. Big paid car park.</li><li><b>Oxford &mdash; the spires:</b> <b>Christ Church</b> (the Harry Potter hall + meadow), the <b>Bodleian</b> &amp; <b>Radcliffe Camera</b>, the tower view from St Mary&rsquo;s, and the <b>Covered Market</b> for lunch. Use a <b>Park &amp; Ride</b> (Pear Tree / Water Eaton) &mdash; city parking is hard.</li><li><b>With Alfie:</b> both outlets are flat and pram-easy; in Oxford the <b>University Parks</b> or Botanic Garden for a run-around and the free, indoor <b>Ashmolean</b> if it&rsquo;s hot. Last car day, so pack that evening.</li></ul></div></details>
      <details class="alt"><summary>&#128260; Alternatives for this day</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>Blenheim Palace, Woodstock</b> (with the Oxford option; ~15 min N of Oxford, on the way home) &mdash; a magnificent UNESCO palace with huge parkland, a playground and a little train. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Blenheim+Palace+Woodstock">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Scenic return via the Cotswolds</b> (Oxford option) &mdash; home through <b>Burford</b> and Chipping Norton instead of the M40; prettier, ~30 min more. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Burford+Cotswolds">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Chester Zoo / Blue Planet</b> (Cheshire Oaks option) &mdash; make it a shopping-plus-animals day; both are right by the outlet. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Chester+Zoo">Map &#8599;</a></li></ul></div></details>
      <div class="links"><a href="https://www.mcarthurglen.com/en/outlets/uk/designer-outlet-cheshire-oaks/">Cheshire Oaks &#8599;</a><a href="https://www.thebicestercollection.com/bicester-village/en">Bicester Village &#8599;</a><a href="https://www.experienceoxfordshire.org/explore/oxford/">Visit Oxford &#8599;</a><a class="ask" href="https://zlviiufrnx354pyk6bc9vy9dauofbwvq.ui.nabu.casa/trip-ask?a=Wednesday%20shopping%20day%20(Cheshire%20Oaks%20vs%20Bicester%20%2B%20Oxford)">Ask for more &#8599;</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="day" data-date="2026-07-16">
    <img loading="lazy" src="data:image/jpeg;base64," alt="Return the car + Birmingham shopping"><div class="cap">Selfridges, the Bullring, Birmingham &middot; Wikimedia Commons</div>
    <div class="body">
      <span class="tag flex">Thu 16 Jul &middot; car back + Birmingham</span>
      <div class="dt">Return the car + Birmingham shopping</div>
      <div class="drive">&#9201; ~30 min to Birmingham &middot; last day with the car</div>
      <p class="desc">The rental goes back today. Drive into Birmingham to drop the SIXT car (check your booking for the exact return depot), then a relaxed afternoon shopping in the centre before the train home. Birmingham&rsquo;s big shopping is all walkable and toddler-friendly, and you&rsquo;re minutes from the station for an easy hop back to Cannock.</p>
      
      
      <details><summary>Car return, shopping &amp; the train home</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>Car return:</b> confirm the SIXT drop-off point and time on your booking (pickup was Birmingham Airport / BHX &mdash; the return is likely the same). Fuel up nearby first if it&rsquo;s a full-to-full deal, and photograph the car at handover.</li><li><b>Shopping:</b> the <b>Bullring</b> (Selfridges, high-street stores) links straight into <b>Grand Central</b> above New Street station (John Lewis-style mix, food hall). All under cover and step-free &mdash; good with a buggy on a hot day.</li><li><b>Break spots with Alfie:</b> St Martin&rsquo;s churchyard green by the Bullring, or the food hall at Grand Central; baby-change facilities in both centres.</li><li><b>Train home:</b> frequent services from <b>New Street</b> (or Birmingham International if you dropped the car at the airport) back towards Cannock &mdash; a short, easy ride. Then pack for Friday&rsquo;s 10:49 London train from Lichfield Trent Valley.</li></ul></div></details>
      <details class="alt"><summary>&#128260; Alternatives for this day</summary><div class="det"><ul><li><b>National SEA LIFE Centre</b>, Brindleyplace (~10 min walk in the centre) &mdash; indoor aquarium, very toddler-friendly. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=National+SEA+LIFE+Centre+Birmingham">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Cadbury World</b>, Bournville (~15 min by train from New Street) &mdash; chocolate tour + a toddler play zone; pre-book. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Cadbury+World+Bournville">Map &#8599;</a></li><li><b>Brindleyplace &amp; the canals</b> &mdash; a flat, pram-easy stroll with cafes and short canal-boat trips, plus the free <b>Library of Birmingham</b> roof garden. <a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Brindleyplace+Birmingham">Map &#8599;</a></li></ul></div></details>
      <div class="links"><a href="https://bullring.co.uk/">Bullring &amp; Grand Central &#8599;</a><a class="map" href="https://www.google.com/maps/dir/Cannock/Birmingham+City+Centre">Directions &#8599;</a><a class="map" href="https://maps.google.com/?q=Grand+Central+Birmingham">Grand Central &#8599;</a><a class="ask" href="https://zlviiufrnx354pyk6bc9vy9dauofbwvq.ui.nabu.casa/trip-ask?a=Birmingham%20(car%20return%20%2B%20shopping)">Ask for more &#8599;</a></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="note" style="margin-top:22px;border-color:#3a5a78;background:#16202c">
    &#127903;&#65039; <b>Then &mdash; London, 17&ndash;19 Jul.</b> After the day-trips week you head down to London (train Fri 17, two nights at the Shard, a South Bank day, home Sun 19). The full illustrated London itinerary is a tap away:
    <div class="links" style="margin-top:8px"><a class="map" href="https://raw.githack.com/paultuddenham/Paul-Sharing-Repo/main/london-jul2026.html">Open the London itinerary &#8599;</a></div>
  </div>
  <div class="note" style="margin-top:22px">
    <b>Backups &amp; swaps</b> (for any of Sat&ndash;Wed, while you have the car): <b>Chester Zoo</b> (~1h, world-class + pram-built), <b>Chatsworth House + Bakewell</b> (~1h, grand house + farmyard/playground), <b>Ironbridge Gorge + Blists Hill</b> (~35 min, a superb pram-friendly Victorian town), the <b>Cotswolds &mdash; Bourton-on-the-Water</b> (~1h15), <b>Trentham Monkey Forest</b> (~35 min), the free <b>National Memorial Arboretum</b> (~20 min), or <b>Shugborough + Lichfield</b> (~15 min, NT estate + cathedral). For Alfie: <b>West Midland Safari Park</b> (~45 min, AC drive-through) or <b>Twycross Zoo</b>. Heat/rain escapes: <b>Waterworld</b> (indoor waterpark), <b>RAF Museum Cosford</b> (free), <b>Conkers</b>. Bigger days out: Warwick Castle, Stratford-upon-Avon, Bridgnorth + Severn Valley steam railway.
  </div>

  <footer>
    Fri 17 Jul &rarr; <a href="https://raw.githack.com/paultuddenham/Paul-Sharing-Repo/main/london-jul2026.html" style="color:var(--acc)">London leg</a> (train 10:49 Lichfield Trent Valley &rarr; Euston) &middot; fly home SQ313 Sun 19 Jul.<br>
    <b>Mileage:</b> the driving days &asymp; <b>600&ndash;670 mi</b> vs your <b>1,050-mi</b> rental allowance &rarr; still clear (the range depends on the Sunday + Wednesday choices). North Wales (~210&ndash;237 mi), the Oxford option (~190 mi) and the Peak District loop (~146 mi) are the biggest chunks &mdash; the big drives are Sun / Tue / Wed, with <b>Monday&rsquo;s Drayton a nice light day in between</b>, so pack for early starts (or take the shorter options).<br>
    Drive times one-way from Cannock, approximate. Photos: Wikimedia Commons. Built by Claude Code 5 Jul; merged toddler + scenery plan 11 Jul 2026. Past days auto-collapse.
  </footer>
</div>
<script>
(function(){
  var t=new Date(); t.setHours(0,0,0,0);
  var days=document.querySelectorAll('.day[data-date]'), past=0;
  days.forEach(function(d){
    var p=d.getAttribute('data-date').split('-');
    var dd=new Date(+p[0],+p[1]-1,+p[2]);
    if(dd<t){ d.classList.add('past'); past++; }
    else if(dd.getTime()===t.getTime()){ d.classList.add('today');
      var b=document.createElement('span'); b.className='badge'; b.textContent='TODAY';
      var dt=d.querySelector('.dt'); if(dt){ dt.appendChild(b); } }
  });
  var btn=document.getElementById('showall');
  if(btn){
    if(past===0){ btn.style.display='none'; }
    else { var lbl='past day'+(past>1?'s':'');
      btn.textContent='Show '+past+' '+lbl;
      btn.addEventListener('click',function(){
        var on=document.body.classList.toggle('show-past');
        btn.textContent=(on?'Hide':'Show '+past)+' '+lbl;
      });
    }
  }
})();
</script>
</body>
</html>